On Fri, 11 Oct 2002 02:47:21 EDT Dnowens@... writes:

>> Tell Dylan I agree with him, he should leave something for the wee
> one who
> lives in his tree. I recommend something warm, it may have been
> years since
> someone left something soft and fluffy for him to wrap up in. Of
> course the
> honey and maybe some nuts. An oatmeal cake would be nice too.
> Homemade bread
> and a bit of butter and/or cheese. Something shiny and new, he may
> not have
> had anything new, all his own, for a long time. A shiny brand new
> penny, or
> maybe a pretty bead? Do you know about those little tiny glass
> beads? (seed
> beads) Have Dylan make a small necklace out of some. Don't forget to
> leave
> something at Samhain!
>
